    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the warning. i'll probably just call someone then. but before i do, is there any way to tell if it's just a cheap part like a capacitor or if the whole motor is fried? i've heard people call these kinds of electrical glitches \"gremlins\" in movies or something, is there any truth to that or is it just a weird noise? i'm just trying to gauge if it's gonna be a huge repair bill or just a small part.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
