      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to call a professional, but you can't really diagnose the difference between a cheap capacitor and a fried motor without specialized tools, so calling someone is the only safe way to find out. The term \"gremlin\" is just a fun movie metaphor for how unpredictable electrical glitches can be, but in reality, these are often just a few specific components failing. A capacitor is a small, inexpensive part that the AC unit uses to start the motor, so if that's the issue, the repair bill will be very low, whereas a seized motor is a much more expensive repair. Since you can't tell just by listening, your best bet is to give a technician a call and let them inspect the unit to give you an accurate quote before they come out.",
